window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A singular act of defiance can change the course of a life.</b></p> <p><i>Award-winning and Amazon best-selling political thriller author Mikael Carlson returns with a tale of heroism, duty, and service inspired by a true story. Fans of the vigilante justice in The Terminal List and the heart-pounding action of Ryan, Reacher, Bourne, and betrayed CIA operative Jason Trapp will love this prequel and the Watchtower Thrillers.</i></p> <p>Emmit “Chicago” Haskins is lost and directionless following his discharge from the 75th Ranger Regiment. While he is staying with his sister in Minneapolis, she suggests that he invite some of his guys over to the house for a barbecue. They could never know what political firestorm awaits.</p> <p>The Minneapolis police changed to become more community-focused following George Floyd’s death. After an ambush that leads police to accidentally shoot innocent bystanders, Landon Tayson and his dedicated group of “reformers” set up an occupied zone that the mayor refuses to dismantle. Most people pass it off as a response to police actions, but is there something more sinister afoot?</p> <p>That’s what Kai Z, a popular podcaster, wants to find out when he sneaks into the newly formed Arts District Occupied Zone. The videos of violent acts he films cause angst for Landon, but it’s Chicago’s defiance of their new laws that the self-appointed president wants to end. After a flag burning leads Chicago to develop an innovative solution to prevent another torching, the leaders of the occupied zone and the Rangers find themselves on a collision course that police are helpless to stop.</p> <p><i>Sua Sponte: The Minneapolis ADOZ</i> follows the plight of five people navigating one of the largest uprisings in American history. Will the Rangers’ dedication to their country lead to a deadly clash with the insurrectionists that will make the streets of this proud American city run red with blood?</p>"; 
